description: AI prompt hygiene and token discipline
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

AI requests should be minimal, contextual, and cost-aware.

Rules:
- send only relevant diff chunks
- include filenames and short context before adding more code
- trim large unchanged context
- chunk long diffs deliberately
- prefer summarization passes over dumping too much text
- use stable prompt templates for each AI feature

Feature prompt intent:
- generate_commit_message: concise, specific, commit-ready
- explain_diff: summarize intent, key changes, risks
- review_staged_changes: identify likely issues, uncertainty allowed

Do not:
- send redundant repeated context
- send unrelated files
- request long essay-style answers
- optimize for verbosity over usefulness